The President held a call with Governors and Mayors from states affected by Hurricane Sandy to express his concern and hear about ongoing response efforts. He thanked the officials for their leadership and praised the emergency response teams. The President directed his team to provide all available resources for the response and recovery efforts. Governors offered assistance to states with more severe impacts, and FEMA was directed to support the movement of these resources. The President's team is working to identify additional assistance to bring power back online faster. The President asked the officials to identify any unmet needs and assured them of constant contact. A list of participants on the call is provided, and senior members of the President's team were present in the Situation Room.